&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HIV Nurse, Band 6 – 22.5 hours per week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lancashire and South Cumbria HIV service is a busy service with a cohort of around 1200 patients. The service is provided by Blackpool Teaching Hospital Trust and provides Clinics across 4 sites in Blackpool, Preston, Burnley, Lancaster and South Cumbria&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated and enthusiastic registered nurse with 1 year post registration experience to be a HIV Nurse in Burnley. Experience working in a sexual health and HIV is desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will provide ongoing care, support, advice, follow-up and information to positive HIV patients within the community setting liaising with other health care professionals as required. They will assist in the assessment, planning, implementation and evaluation of nursing care of patients diagnosed with sexually transmitted infections and HIV. The post holder will provide information, education and training to health care professionals and others as required regarding HIV. The post holder will work closely with the HIV service manager and Clinical nurse specialists in each locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate must have excellent communication skills, both written and verbal. They will need to be well organised and to be able to manage a busy work schedule. They will be expected to work in both the Acute Trust and the Community/Outreach setting. The post holder will be expected to act as a role model for all staff and contribute to the development and training needs of staff both within and outside the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
